---
/**
 * How it works — three steps, each one a beat in the scroll narrative playing
 * out on the constellation behind this section (brain/index.ts reads the
 * data-beat markers to time the scrub):
 *   connect → the network is the factory's history
 *   search  → a target color enters, retrieval propagates (data-beat="search")
 *   recommend → the matched recipe flares (data-beat="match")
 *   silence → the network dims and stills (data-beat="abstain")
 */
---

<section class="how stage-panel" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="how__head reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it works · no new hardware</p>
      <h2 class="title">Three steps. Zero new process.</h2>
    </div>

    <ol class="how__steps">
      <li class="how__step reveal" data-beat="connect">
        <span class="how__num">01</span>
        <h3>Connect</h3>
        <p>
          Share your historical batch records. Every dye job you've ever run
          becomes a point in color space — the more history, the sharper and
          more substrate-specific the match.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="how__step how__step--right reveal" data-beat="search">
        <span class="how__num">02</span>
        <h3>Search</h3>
        <p>
          A new target color drops into the map. Color Brain finds the closest
          proven recipe on the same substrate and scores how likely it is to
          beat your technician's first attempt.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="how__step reveal" data-beat="match">
        <span class="how__num">03</span>
        <h3>Recommend</h3>
        <p>
          Above the calibrated confidence gate, you get a real recipe your
          factory already ran — batch number, evidence, and win probability
          included.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <!-- The abstention moment: color drains, motion stills, one line stands. -->
  <div class="how__silence" data-beat="abstain">
    <p class="how__silence-line reveal">
      And when it isn't sure&thinsp;—&thinsp;it says nothing.
    </p>
    <p class="how__silence-sub reveal">
      Abstention is a trust feature, not a miss. A recommendation you can act
      on, or calibrated silence.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .how {
    padding-top: var(--section-pad);
  }

  .how__steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .how__step {
    min-height: 78vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    max-width: 26rem;
  }

  .how__step--right {
    margin-left: auto;
  }

  .how__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  }

  .how__step h3 {
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
  }

  .how__step p {
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .how__silence {
    min-height: 90vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding-inline: var(--gutter);
  }

  .how__silence-line {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.4vw, 2.6rem);
    color: var(--abstain);
    max-width: 24ch;
  }

  .how__silence-sub {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 44ch;
  }
</style>
